		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">This project aims to explore the application of program transformation to the process of re-engineering large software systems. In particular, we aim to develop methods for raising the level of abstraction of legacy systems, including programs written in assembler, to the point where high level specifications for the programs are obtained, which are suitable for refinement into a different programming language. One application of this approach is in migration from assembler language to a modern high-level language such as Java, but there are many other benefits of design recovery and rapid re-engineering of large-scale systems to meet new requirements. To evaluate our theory, we will apply it to various large-scale case studies from the manufacturing and financial industrial sectors. In the long run, the ultimate beneficiaries of this research are any organisations who need to handle constant changes in both system requirements and environments efficiently and economically.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
